But for all the progress Bank of America has made in recovering from the losses of the financial crisis, investors have been punishing the bank’s shares. During a wider decline in the market, Bank of America’s shares have dropped 29 percent since the start of the year. The shares of large banks have dropped more sharply than the broader stock market.Even with his pay raise, Mr. Moynihan remains on the lower end of the compensation scale among Wall Street chief executives.JPMorgan Chase increased Jamie Dimon’s pay package 35 percent to $27 million last year.Lloyd C. Blankfein, chief of Goldman Sachs, saw his pay package reduced for the first time since 2011. Last year, his pay was $23 million, $1 million less than he made in 2014.At Morgan Stanley, James P. Gorman’s compensation as chief decreased to $21 million, from $22.5 million.
Continue reading the main story






